THE Minister for Communication and Information Technology, Dr Faustine Ndugulile has said the ministry aims at improving  government ICT systems to reduce public complaints while protecting user’s online information. He said the improvement of the  communication technology   must also go hand in hand with  strengthening of  the  ICT systems  to avoid being hacked  by people with evil  intentions. Speaking in Dodoma today the minister  said the objective of improving the systems is to enable users to use them  correctly while achieving the  intended goals. The minister has said it’s the ministry’s responsibility to ensure that it controls malicious individuals who abuse ICT systems, adding that the government  has already noticed gross misuse of technology.